OL,3,CCalls for older Channel Islands'
OL,4,Cdrivers to have compulsory eye tests
OL,6,FSome across the Channel Islands say
OL,7,Fthey would like to see similar
OL,8,Flegislation introduced.
OL,10,FJohn Bichard's been driving taxis in
OL,11,FGuernsey for 32 years and says he
OL,12,Foften sees motorists who he thinks
OL,13,Fdemonstrate signs of failing eyesight.
OL,15,F"You may not know or think you've got
OL,16,Fa problem but people from the outside
OL,17,Fcan see," he says.
