OL,3,CCalls for older Channel Islands'
OL,4,Cdrivers to have compulsory eye tests
OL,6,FJohn adds that taxi drivers on-island
OL,7,Fhave to complete compulsory eye tests
OL,8,Fonce they're over the age of 65, and
OL,9,Fthere could be great benefit to others
OL,10,Fdoing something similar.
OL,12,F"I love my freedom", he explains. "I
OL,13,Funderstand why people don't want that
OL,14,Ftaken away.
OL,16,F"Driving has been my life, so I would
OL,17,Ffeel the same, but if I needed to have
OL,18,Feye checks done, glasses, cataracts,
OL,19,Fwhatever to continue driving, then I
OL,20,Fthink you should."
