OL,3,CCalls for older Channel Islands'
OL,4,Cdrivers to have compulsory eye tests
OL,6,FBut when it comes to getting behind
OL,7,Fthe wheel, Jacqui thinks the dangers
OL,8,Fare heightened.
OL,10,F"You never know when someone is going
OL,11,Fto pull out in front of you," she
OL,12,Fexplains. "You never know when that
OL,13,Fpedestrian is going to come into the
OL,14,Froad.
OL,16,F"Low contrast - when we start hitting
OL,17,Fdusks and late at night - if you've
OL,18,Fgot an early cataract, that can make
OL,19,Fthings far more difficult for you to
OL,20,Fsee."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/9
