OL,3,CCalls for older Channel Islands'
OL,4,Cdrivers to have compulsory eye tests
OL,6,FHowever, the UK is one of only three
OL,7,FEuropean countries to rely on self-
OL,8,Freporting for eyesight problems that
OL,9,Faffect driving so the Channel Islands
OL,10,Fare in the minority.
OL,12,FWhether or not the Channel Islands
OL,13,Fchoose to follow the UK's lead remains
OL,14,Fto be seen.
OL,16,FGuernsey's Traffic and Highway
OL,17,FServices say they will "liaise with
OL,18,Four counterparts at the UK Driver
OL,19,FVehicle and Licensing Agency about
OL,20,Fthis and monitor how these proposals
OL,21,Fdevelop".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/9
